        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The “Subsidy on Annual Auction of Notified Waters” is a scheme component under the Scheme for the Welfare of Scheduled Caste Families in the Fisheries Sector, launched by the Fisheries Department, Government of Haryana. The objective of the scheme is to provide full-time employment to individuals from Scheduled Caste families in the fisheries sector and uplift their socio-economic status by promoting fish farming through subsidization of fishing contract costs in designated water bodies. Under this scheme, a subsidy of up to 50% of the actual auctioned amount of notified water bodies is provided to Scheduled Caste beneficiaries to help them acquire fishing rights in such notified waters.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- 50% subsidy of the actual auctioned amount with maximum limit of ₹5,00,000/- per auction, whichever is less.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The objective of the scheme is to provide full-time employment to individuals from Scheduled Caste families in the fisheries sector and uplift their socio-economic status by promoting fish farming through subsidization of fishing contract costs in designated water bodies. ",
        "exclusions_md": "\n- The applicant must not be a Government/ Semi-Government employee. \n\n<br>\n\n",
